subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Plate 11
). Uncus bluntly pointed, socius with apex broadened and bluntly pointed, valva with costa concave, a small spine on terminal edge, saccus with a clubbed end.

Female genitalia (
Plate 21
). Lobes of lamella postvaginalis gently curved, ostium small, ostial chamber almost cylindrical then abruptly contracted into ductus, ductus longer than abdomen, corpus bursae ovate, signum cruciform with short spines on transverse section.
